<br>
To a certain extend.  Obviously there are going to be limits, like someone couldn't go around calling people racial epitaphs or threatening to kill someone.  Just like you can't yell fire in a theatre.  They might need to close a thread here or there in cases where people &quot;cross the line&quot;.<br>
<br>
A perfect example of bad modding... the final warning thread.  It should have been closed immediately after it was posted.  I can almost see the need to post that someone was on their final warning (I did say almost), but it should have been closed off there.  I would prefer an email to the person.  Same with banning.  No need to flog someone publically (really, banning shouldn't ever happen unless someone goes way over the edge, hurting others or threatening to hurt others).  Definately no need for morons to discuss how big an idiot the person in question is.<br>
<br>
Zel<br>
